      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "It's heartbreaking to see your children's stress and frustration, especially when you can relate to their feelings. It's natural to feel like you're being a burden, but try to reframe your thinking - you're not a problem, you're a parent who loves and cares deeply. Instead of wishing to be less of a burden, try to focus on being present and available to support them in the ways they need, even if it's just having a conversation or a listening ear. You can't control how others feel, but you can control how you show up for them.",
      "source": "target",
